    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2>Project Overview</h2>\n<p>In Electronic Power Steering (EPS) systems, bolted joints are safety-critical components subject to complex dynamic loads. Traditional analytical verification according to the <strong>VDI 2230</strong> standard often relies on significant approximations for complex geometries. This research modernized the verification process by developing a model-based FEM approach that captures localized stress distributions and clamping force behavior with high precision.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 700px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/portfolio/static/19ce669b4e3b2665b95108c417194732/4466a/steering.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 77.71428571428571%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Architectural Components of the EPS Steering Assembly\"\n        title=\"Architectural Components of the EPS Steering Assembly\"\n        src=\"/portfolio/static/19ce669b4e3b2665b95108c417194732/39600/steering.png\"\n        srcset=\"/portfolio/static/19ce669b4e3b2665b95108c417194732/1aaec/steering.png 175w,\n/portfolio/static/19ce669b4e3b2665b95108c417194732/98287/steering.png 350w,\n/portfolio/static/19ce669b4e3b2665b95108c417194732/39600/steering.png 700w,\n/portfolio/static/19ce669b4e3b2665b95108c417194732/57cd1/steering.png 1050w,\n/portfolio/static/19ce669b4e3b2665b95108c417194732/4af54/steering.png 1400w,\n/portfolio/static/19ce669b4e3b2665b95108c417194732/4466a/steering.png 1740w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><em>Figure 1: Identification of critical bolted joint locations in steering housing assemblies</em></p>\n<h3>High-Fidelity Automation Workflow</h3>\n<p>The core of this project was the development of a custom <strong>ABAQUS Plug-In</strong> using the Python API. This tool automates a rigorous 14-step engineering pipeline, ensuring consistency across various design iterations:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Multi-Model Transition:</strong> The workflow handles the transition from high-complexity <strong>Model Class III</strong> (capturing full geometric interaction) to simplified <strong>Model Class I</strong> (standardized analysis) to perform precise safety checks.</li>\n<li><strong>Load Case Automation:</strong> Integrated handling of assembly preloads, thermal effects, and operational load cases into a single input stream.</li>\n<li><strong>Verification Logic:</strong> Automated extraction of field and history outputs to verify working stress, assembly stress, and minimum length of engagement.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 700px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/portfolio/static/1f0bc98b04c5c5d09e05e86ff9003248/baba4/fc2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 118.85714285714286%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The 14-Step Automated Verification Pipeline\"\n        title=\"The 14-Step Automated Verification Pipeline\"\n        src=\"/portfolio/static/1f0bc98b04c5c5d09e05e86ff9003248/39600/fc2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/portfolio/static/1f0bc98b04c5c5d09e05e86ff9003248/1aaec/fc2.png 175w,\n/portfolio/static/1f0bc98b04c5c5d09e05e86ff9003248/98287/fc2.png 350w,\n/portfolio/static/1f0bc98b04c5c5d09e05e86ff9003248/39600/fc2.png 700w,\n/portfolio/static/1f0bc98b04c5c5d09e05e86ff9003248/57cd1/fc2.png 1050w,\n/portfolio/static/1f0bc98b04c5c5d09e05e86ff9003248/baba4/fc2.png 1346w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><em>Figure 2: Workflow logic for the ABAQUS automation plug-in</em></p>\n<h3>Engineering Validation</h3>\n<p>The accuracy of the automated FEA script was verified against classical VDI 2230 analytical calculations using a connecting rod benchmark. The results demonstrated a near-perfect correlation, validating the script’s ability to replace manual calculations for complex parts.</p>\n<div style=\"overflow-x: auto; margin: 3em 0;\">\n  <table style=\"width: 100%; table-layout: fixed; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.95em;\">\n    <thead>\n      <tr style=\"background-color: var(--light-navy); border-bottom: 2px solid var(--green);\">\n        <th style=\"width: 40%; text-align: left; padding: 20px; color: var(--green);\">Quantity</th>\n        <th style=\"width: 20%; text-align: center; padding: 20px; color: var(--green);\">Analytical<br/>(VDI 2230)</th>\n        <th style=\"width: 20%; text-align: center; padding: 20px 20px 20px 60px; color: var(--green);\">FEM-based<br/>Script</th>\n        <th style=\"width: 20%; text-align: right; padding: 20px; color: var(--green);\">Relative<br/>Change</th>\n      </tr>\n    </thead>\n    <tbody>\n      <tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid var(--lightest-navy);\">\n        <td style=\"text-align: left; padding: 20px;\">Min required clamp load (F<sub>KQ</sub>)</td>\n        <td style=\"text-align: center; padding: 20px; font-family: var(--font-mono);\">16267 N</td>\n        <td style=\"text-align: center; padding: 20px 20px 20px 60px; font-family: var(--font-mono);\">16155.43 N</td>\n        <td style=\"text-align: right; padding: 20px; font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--green);\"><strong>-0.69%</strong></td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid var(--lightest-navy);\">\n        <td style=\"text-align: left; padding: 20px;\">Embedding (f<sub>z</sub>)</td>\n        <td style=\"text-align: center; padding: 20px; font-family: var(--font-mono);\">1103 N</td>\n        <td style=\"text-align: center; padding: 20px 20px 20px 60px; font-family: var(--font-mono);\">1100.89 N</td>\n        <td style=\"text-align: right; padding: 20px; font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--green);\"><strong>-0.20%</strong></td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td style=\"text-align: left; padding: 20px;\">Safety margin working stress (S<sub>F</sub>)</td>\n        <td style=\"text-align: center; padding: 20px; font-family: var(--font-mono);\">1.43</td>\n        <td style=\"text-align: center; padding: 20px 20px 20px 60px; font-family: var(--font-mono);\">1.42</td>\n        <td style=\"text-align: right; padding: 20px; font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--green);\"><strong>+0.70%</strong></td>\n      </tr>\n    </tbody>\n  </table>\n</div>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 700px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/portfolio/static/8318b0df23053f3d1e7ac73b09fc0e2e/1d4c8/pull.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 46.857142857142854%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Experimental Pull-Out Test vs. Simulation Model\"\n        title=\"Experimental Pull-Out Test vs. Simulation Model\"\n        src=\"/portfolio/static/8318b0df23053f3d1e7ac73b09fc0e2e/39600/pull.png\"\n        srcset=\"/portfolio/static/8318b0df23053f3d1e7ac73b09fc0e2e/1aaec/pull.png 175w,\n/portfolio/static/8318b0df23053f3d1e7ac73b09fc0e2e/98287/pull.png 350w,\n/portfolio/static/8318b0df23053f3d1e7ac73b09fc0e2e/39600/pull.png 700w,\n/portfolio/static/8318b0df23053f3d1e7ac73b09fc0e2e/57cd1/pull.png 1050w,\n/portfolio/static/8318b0df23053f3d1e7ac73b09fc0e2e/4af54/pull.png 1400w,\n/portfolio/static/8318b0df23053f3d1e7ac73b09fc0e2e/1d4c8/pull.png 1412w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><em>Figure 3: Physical validation through pull-out testing to establish failure limits</em></p>\n<h3>Material Hardness &#x26; 100% Conservativeness</h3>\n<p>A critical finding of the research addressed the non-conservative behavior of AlSi12 aluminum alloys. To ensure a fail-safe design, the workflow was refined using experimental data to establish a hardness-based shear limit relationship:</p>\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>&tau;<sub>B</sub> / HB = 1.5</strong></p>\n<p>By integrating this correlation into the minimum length of engagement calculation, the tool achieved <strong>100% conservativeness</strong>. This refinement ensures that the automated verification consistently identifies the lower bound of structural integrity, providing a reliable safety margin for mass-production steering assemblies.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 700px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/portfolio/static/9a557a3cfc0152b92cb613a54354747a/5d78e/p1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 34.285714285714285%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Stress Gradient Comparison at Failure Limits\"\n        title=\"Stress Gradient Comparison at Failure Limits\"\n        src=\"/portfolio/static/9a557a3cfc0152b92cb613a54354747a/39600/p1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/portfolio/static/9a557a3cfc0152b92cb613a54354747a/1aaec/p1.png 175w,\n/portfolio/static/9a557a3cfc0152b92cb613a54354747a/98287/p1.png 350w,\n/portfolio/static/9a557a3cfc0152b92cb613a54354747a/39600/p1.png 700w,\n/portfolio/static/9a557a3cfc0152b92cb613a54354747a/57cd1/p1.png 1050w,\n/portfolio/static/9a557a3cfc0152b92cb613a54354747a/4af54/p1.png 1400w,\n/portfolio/static/9a557a3cfc0152b92cb613a54354747a/5d78e/p1.png 2466w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><em>Figure 4: Validation of FEM results with experimental and checking for the conservativeness of the model</em></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Automated FEA Strength Verification of Bolted Joints","description":"Architected a 14-step automated Python workflow for the high-fidelity verification of safety-critical bolted joints in EPS systems, achieving 100% conservativeness through hardness-based material optimization.","date":"2021-06","slug":"/featured/bolt-analysis","tags":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/featured/bolt-analysis"}},
